bilingual.source: He is expected to be present at the exhibition.
With the new hatchlings, the population is expected to grow.
bilingual.target: 随着新孵化的幼龟，预计种群数量将会增加。

bilingual.source: Showers are expected to clear up by evening.
bilingual.target: 阵雨预计将在傍晚结束。

bilingual.source: The investment is expected to return a profit.
bilingual.target: 这项投资预计会返回利润。

bilingual.source: The building is expected to be completed next year.
bilingual.target: 这座大楼预计明年竣工。

bilingual.source: Please inform us of the expected time of delivery.
bilingual.target: 请告知我们预计的交货期。

bilingual.source: The project is expected to be completed next month.
bilingual.target: 这个项目预计下个月脱稿。

bilingual.source: Temperatures are expected to soar over the weekend.
bilingual.target: 预计周末气温将急剧上升。

bilingual.source: The ship is expected toa at the port by noon.
bilingual.target: 预计这艘船将在中午到达港口。

bilingual.source: The investment is expected to yeld high returns.
bilingual.target: 预计这项投资将产出高回报。

yingyinNormal.en: By 2030, 350 million people, the population of the United States, are expected to move from the countryside to the cities.
yingyinNormal.zh: 到2030年，预计有三亿五千万人，相当于美国的人口总量，将会从农村迁移到城市。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, that's not a surprise at all. I mean, if I knew you were good at surprises, I would have expected the surprise, and therefore not have been surprised.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那根本不算惊喜，如果我本来就知道你擅长给人惊喜，那我就会预计到有这个惊喜，然后就不会被你“惊喜到”。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, that went better than expected.
yingyinNormal.zh: 比预料的情况要好。

yingyinNormal.en: Adversity is to be expected. Continue.
yingyinNormal.zh: 万事开头难，继续。

yingyinNormal.en: You're not what I expected, Mr Holmes. You're nicer.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你跟我想的不一样，福尔摩斯先生。你要更好些。

yingyinNormal.en: As expected, she was unable to complete the puzzle at all.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不出所料，她根本无法完成游戏。
yingyinNormal.videoNameEn: 《Rise of the Planet of the Apes》

yingyinNormal.en: Thank you for the video. That wasn't what I expected to see.
yingyinNormal.zh: 谢谢你们做的视频，我真没想到。

yingyinNormal.en: I never expected you'd want me. I thought I was just a placeholder.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我没想到你会想要我，我以为我只是个占座的。

yingyinNormal.en: You can't even break a rule. How would you be expected to break bone?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你甚至都不敢打破规矩，又怎么敢去抛头颅洒热血?

yingyinNormal.en: I can't believe you told her. You just expected me to keep it a secret?
yingyinNormal.zh: 真不敢相信你告诉她了。你希望我保守秘密？

yingyinNormal.en: I get to kill Snow. I expected no less of you. Then I vote yes for Prim.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我要亲手处决斯诺。肯定的。那我同意，为了波丽姆。

yingyinNormal.en: You know what, Mr. Fredricksen? The wilderness isn't quite what I expected.
yingyinNormal.zh: 知道吗， Fredricksen先生? 我所期望的荒野并不是这样的。

yingyinNormal.en: I must say, Juliana, you're the last person I expected to see here tonight.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我必须说，朱莉安娜，我今晚绝对没想到会在这里见到你。

yingyinNormal.en: We expected them to be conservative in the sexual preferences and they were.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们也预测他们的性偏好会较为保守，事实与预测一致。

yingyinNormal.en: I can't be expected to do all the thinking in this army, can I, Bean? No, sir!
yingyinNormal.zh: 战队不能只依靠我一个人的想法，对吧，小豆子，没错。

yingyinNormal.en: Cooper, we have a problem. Your work is really not at a level I expected it to be.
yingyinNormal.zh: 库珀，我们得聊聊，你的研究可真是没达到我原以为的水准啊。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, yes. In my culture, it's expected to have a chaperone to oversee a first date.
yingyinNormal.zh: 确定。按照我们的习俗，相亲时就得带个伴来帮过过眼。

yingyinNormal.en: Did you know the kind of work you'd be expected to do? They were looking for guards.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你知不知道你要做的是什么工作？他们在找看守。

yingyinNormal.en: It's so wonderful to see you again, my dear, in fact I hardly expected to see so much.
yingyinNormal.zh: 很高兴又看到你了，亲爱的，老实说 我没想到会看到那么多。

yingyinNormal.en: And when the Earth was moving in the opposite direction, they expected it to go slower.
yingyinNormal.zh: 而且，当地球与光束作反方向移动时，光的速度会减慢。

word_level_phrase_info.brief_definition: 预期的；不出所料；正如预期的

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: Use of their gut hurt their performance on the first four tasks, as <highlight>expected</highlight>, and helped them on the rest.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 正如预期的那样，使用他们的直觉会影响他们在前四项任务中的表现，但却会帮助他们完成余下的任务。

examination_example.sentence: They are more sensitive to social cues than <highlight>expected</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们对社交暗示比预期更敏感。

examination_example.sentence: Detailed plans may not be as fruitful as <highlight>expected</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 详细的计划可能不会像预期的那样富有成效。
